oauth.title: OAuth Configuration
oauth.instructions: Follow the steps to complete OAuth authorization
proxy.title: Proxy Configuration
stats.title: Account Statistics
help.proxy_settings: Configure a proxy to route requests
help.priority: Priority for account selection (higher = more priority)
form.account_name_placeholder: Set an easy-to-identify name for the account
form.account_type_help: Shared Account: for use by all API Keys; Dedicated Account: only for specific API Keys; Group Scheduling: join group for scheduling within the group
form.expiry_help: Set Claude Max/Pro subscription expiry date, scheduling will stop after expiry
form.gemini_project_id_title: Google Cloud/Workspace account needs to provide Project ID
form.gemini_project_id_help: Some Google accounts (especially those linked to Google Cloud) will be identified as Workspace accounts and need to provide an additional Project ID.
form.gemini_project_id_step2: Copy the Project ID, usually in string format
form.gemini_project_id_warning: Note: copy the Project ID, not the Project Number!
form.gemini_project_id_tip: Tip: if your account is a normal personal account (not linked to Google Cloud), leave this field blank.
form.bedrock_region_tip: Please enter the full region code, such as us-east-1
form.bedrock_session_token_placeholder: If using temporary credentials, enter session token
form.bedrock_session_token_help: Only needs to be filled when using temporary AWS credentials
form.bedrock_default_model_help: If left blank, system default will be used. Supports Inference Profile ID or ARN
form.bedrock_model_help_list: Supports Inference Profile ID (recommended)|Supports Application Inference Profile ARN|Common model: us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-20250514-v1:0|If left blank, system configured default will be used
form.bedrock_small_fast_model_help: Lightweight model for fast response, system default will be used if left blank
form.azure_endpoint_help: Azure OpenAI resource endpoint URL, format: https://your-resource.openai.azure.com
form.azure_api_version_help: Azure OpenAI API version, defaults to latest stable version 2024-02-01
form.azure_deployment_name_help: Deployment name created in Azure OpenAI Studio
form.azure_supported_models_help: Select model types supported by this deployment
form.rate_limit_enabled_help: When enabled, scheduling will pause for a period when account returns 429 error
form.rate_limit_minutes_help: Scheduling pause time after account is rate limited (minutes)
form.daily_quota_help: Set daily usage quota, 0 means no limit
form.quota_reset_time_help: Time to automatically reset daily quota
form.max_concurrent_help: Limit concurrent request count for this account, 0 means no limit
form.model_whitelist_help: Select models allowed to use this account. Leave blank means support all models.
form.model_mapping_help: Configure model mapping relationships. Left is client requested model, right is actual model sent to API.
form.custom_user_agent_placeholder: If left blank, client User-Agent is passed through
form.custom_user_agent_help: When left blank, client User-Agent will be used automatically, only fill when need to fix specific UA
form.openai_responses_base_url_help: Third-party OpenAI compatible API base URL, do not include specific paths
form.openai_responses_api_key_help: API key provided by third-party service
form.openai_responses_user_agent_placeho: If left blank, original request User-Agent is passed through
form.openai_responses_user_agent_help: Optional. If set, all requests will use this User-Agent; otherwise pass through client User-Agent
form.gemini_api_base_url_help: Fill in API base URL (can include path prefix), system will concatenate automatically
form.gemini_api_key_help: API key obtained from Google AI Studio
form.subscription_pro_note: Pro account does not support Claude Opus 4 model
form.auto_stop_5h_limit: Automatically stop scheduling when 5-hour usage nears limit
form.auto_stop_5h_limit_help: When system detects account nearing 5-hour usage limit, will automatically pause scheduling. Will resume automatically when entering new time window.
form.unified_claude_version_help: When enabled, will use unified User-Agent captured from real Claude Code client, improving compatibility
form.waiting_for_capture: Waiting for Claude Code client capture
form.capture_tip: Tip: if not captured for a long time, confirm there is a Claude Code client using this account, or contact developer to verify if User-Agent format has changed
form.unified_client_id_help: When enabled, will use fixed client identifier, making all requests appear from same client, reducing characteristics
form.client_id_help: This ID will replace the client user_id part in request, preserving session part for sticky session
form.scheduling_priority_help: Lower number = higher priority, suggested range: 1-100
form.manual_token_claude_help: Enter valid Claude Access Token. If you have Refresh Token, it is recommended to fill it as well to support automatic refresh.
form.manual_token_gemini_help: Enter valid Gemini Access Token. If you have Refresh Token, it is recommended to fill it as well to support automatic refresh.
form.manual_token_openai_help: Enter valid OpenAI Access Token. If you have Refresh Token, it is recommended to fill it as well to support automatic refresh.
form.manual_token_droid_help: Enter valid Droid Access Token, and also provide Refresh Token to support automatic refresh.
form.claude_token_source: Get from machine with Claude Code logged in
form.claude_token_file: credentials file, do not use key from Claude official website API Keys page.
form.gemini_token_source: Get from machine with Gemini CLI logged in
form.openai_token_source: Get authentication credentials from machine with OpenAI account logged in, or get Access Token through OAuth authorization process
form.droid_token_source: Get Access Token and Refresh Token from credentials exported from Droid CLI or Factory.ai
form.no_refresh_token_warning: If Refresh Token is not filled, Token will need to be manually updated after expiration.
form.droid_refresh_token_required: Droid account must fill Refresh Token, lack of this will cause inability to automatically refresh Access Token.
form.access_token_optional_placeholder: Optional: if not filled, system will get automatically through Refresh Token...
form.access_token_optional_help: Access Token is optional. If not provided, system will get automatically through Refresh Token.
form.refresh_token_claude_help: System will use Refresh Token to automatically get Access Token and user information
form.refresh_token_droid_help: System will use Refresh Token to automatically refresh Factory.ai access token, ensuring account stays available.
form.droid_api_key_mode: Use API Key to Schedule Droid
form.droid_api_key_mode_help: Fill one or more Factory.ai API Keys, system will randomly select when requesting and maintain stickiness combined with session hash, ensuring conversation context stays stable.
form.droid_api_key_list_placeholder: One API Key per line, can paste multiple lines
form.droid_api_key_list_help: Recommended to provide independent quota for each Key; system will deduplicate automatically and ignore blank lines.
form.droid_allocation_strategy_1: New session will randomly select a Key and maintain stickiness during session validity period.
form.droid_allocation_strategy_2: If a Key fails, will automatically switch to remaining available Keys, maximizing success rate.
form.droid_allocation_strategy_3: If upstream returns 4xx error code, that Key will be automatically marked as abnormal; after all Keys are abnormal, account will pause.
form.setup_token_instructions: Follow the steps below to complete Claude account authorization through Setup Token:
form.setup_token_step1: Click button below to generate authorization link
form.setup_token_step2_title: Open link in browser and complete authorization
form.setup_token_step2_help: Open authorization link in new tab, log in to your Claude account and authorize Claude Code.
form.setup_token_proxy_note: Note: if you configured a proxy, make sure browser also uses same proxy to access authorization page.
form.setup_token_step3_help: After completing authorization, copy authorization code from return page and paste in input box below:
form.setup_token_code_placeholder: Paste authorization code obtained from Claude Code authorization page...
form.setup_token_code_help: Paste authorization code copied from Claude Code authorization page
form.leave_blank_no_update_api_key: Leave blank means no update to API Key
